cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SY, cs.GR. 

This paper deals with a geometric data structure problem of finding the largest disk containing a query point in logarithmic time with linear storage. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a data structure of size O(n) and constructs it in O(n log^3 n) time, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The logarithmic time complexity of the query algorithm indicates that it may also be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the problem of finding the largest disk containing a query point can be considered a graph problem, which may make it relevant to cs.GR (Computer Science and Game Theory).
